<subSubSection id="1D82655B3168FFA1FFEBD92F5288FBD7" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="552736D03168FFA1FFEBD92F5164FDF7" blockId="5.[113,1089,314,1041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FFEBD92F50EBFE97" bold="true" box="[113,230,314,337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A medium-sized keroplatid fungus gnat with unmarked wings and with posterior third of its abdomen bent ventrally. Three ocelli in a triangular position. Median ocellus distinctly smaller, rudimentary. Antennae with cylindrical flagellomeres, each flagellomere about as long as wide or shorter. Mouthparts strongly reduced, palpus with only two short palpomeres. Wing transparent, brownish, without markings. Vein R4 absent. Stem of M-fork relatively long, about half as long as M2. Cu1 distinctly curved towards the tip. A1 weak, not reaching wing margin. Terminalia with a long aedeagal complex, reaching internally to the 7 
<superScript id="A2ED9B983168FFA1FFE5DA0D5086FDE0" attach="left" box="[127,139,536,550]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">th</superScript>
abdominal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="552736D03168FFA1FFEBDA2F5288FBD7" blockId="5.[113,1089,314,1041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FFEBDA2F5166FD97" bold="true" box="[113,363,570,593]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new genus differs from most genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FCFDDA2F53FCFD97" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[871,1009,570,593]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Keroplatidae</taxonomicName>
mainly in wing characters, such as the absence of R4, long stem of M-fork, strongly downcurved vein Cu1 and reduced A1. It is similar in most characters to the recently described Neotropical genus 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FF46DA8F5235FD77" authority="Sevcik, 2012" authorityName="Sevcik" authorityYear="2012" box="[220,568,666,689]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Pseudochetoneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FF46DA8F51AFFD77" box="[220,418,666,689]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Pseudochetoneura</emphasis>
Ševčík, 2012
</taxonomicName>
, especially in overall habitus, shape of antennae, reduced palpi, ventrally bent abdomen and the outline of the male terminalia, especially the long apodeme of aedeagal complex. 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FE6ADACF5282FD37" authority="Ševčík &amp; Mantič &amp; Blagoderov, 2015" authorityName="Ševčík &amp; Mantič &amp; Blagoderov" authorityYear="2015" box="[496,655,730,753]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Asiokeroplatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FE6ADACF5282FD37" box="[496,655,730,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Asiokeroplatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7CDF57B93168FFA1FD09DACF52FEFD37" box="[659,755,730,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FCE0DACF544DFD37" authorityName="Sevcik" authorityYear="2012" box="[890,1088,730,753]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Pseudochetoneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FCE0DACF544DFD37" box="[890,1088,730,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Pseudochetoneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly in distinctly larger body size and in different wing venation (basal cell and R-M fusion are strongly reduced in 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FEEADB0F523BFCF7" authorityName="Sevcik" authorityYear="2012" box="[368,566,794,817]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Pseudochetoneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FEEADB0F523BFCF7" box="[368,566,794,817]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Pseudochetoneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The bent male abdomen and the long aedeagal complex in these two genera are reminiscent of those of 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FD5DDB2F53C1FC97" authority="Edwards, 1929" authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1929" box="[711,972,826,849]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Urytalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FD5DDB2F532AFC97" box="[711,807,826,849]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Urytalpa</emphasis>
Edwards, 1929
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FC40DB2F5434FC97" authorityName="Matile" authorityYear="1990" box="[986,1081,826,849]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Orfeliini">Orfeliini</taxonomicName>
) but in the other characters (mainly on the head and wing) they are sufficiently different. In the wing venation, 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FEDADB6F51D2FC57" authority="Ševčík &amp; Mantič &amp; Blagoderov, 2015" authorityName="Ševčík &amp; Mantič &amp; Blagoderov" authorityYear="2015" box="[320,479,890,913]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Asiokeroplatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FEDADB6F51D2FC57" box="[320,479,890,913]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Asiokeroplatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7CDF57B93168FFA1FE7DDB6F5244FC57" box="[487,585,890,913]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shows also some similarities with the Oriental 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FFEBDB8F5172FC77" authority="Colless, 1962" authorityName="Colless" authorityYear="1962" box="[113,383,922,945]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Chetoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FFEBDB8F50E0FC77" box="[113,237,922,945]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Chetoneura</emphasis>
Colless, 1962
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FE37DB8F5337FC77" authority="Sevcik &amp; Papp, 2009" authorityName="Sevcik &amp; Papp" authorityYear="2009" box="[429,826,922,945]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Microkeroplatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FE37DB8F5254FC77" box="[429,601,922,945]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Microkeroplatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="31094B213168FFA1FDC4DB8F5337FC77" author="SEVCIK J. &amp; PAPP L." box="[606,826,922,945]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" pagination="339 - 347" refId="ref6165" refString="SEVCIK J. &amp; PAPP L. 2009: Microkeroplatus, a new genus of Keroplatidae (Diptera) from the Oriental region. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 55: 339 - 347." type="journal article" year="2009">Ševčík &amp; Papp, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but both the latter genera have quite different male terminalia and antennae (see 
<bibRefCitation id="31094B213168FFA1FD20DBAF5341FC17" author="SEVCIK J." box="[698,844,954,977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" pagination="281 - 288" refId="ref6041" refString="SEVCIK J. 2012 a: Pseudochetoneura gen. nov., a peculiar new genus from Ecuador, with notes on Chetoneura (Diptera: Keroplatidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 52: 281 - 288." type="journal article" year="2012">ŠEVČÍK 2012a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="31094B213168FFA1FCCDDBAF543FFC17" author="SEVCIK J. &amp; PAPP L." box="[855,1074,954,977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" pagination="339 - 347" refId="ref6165" refString="SEVCIK J. &amp; PAPP L. 2009: Microkeroplatus, a new genus of Keroplatidae (Diptera) from the Oriental region. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 55: 339 - 347." type="journal article" year="2009">ŠEVČÍK &amp; PAPP 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FFEBDBCF50FDFC37" bold="true" box="[113,240,986,1009]" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from Asia, referring to its distribution, and 
<taxonomicName id="92984D533168FFA1FC57DBCF50E1FBD7" authority="Bosc, 1792" authorityName="Bosc" authorityYear="1792" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Keroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67ECEAC23168FFA1FC57DBCF544DFC37" box="[973,1088,986,1009]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Keroplatus</emphasis>
Bosc, 1792
</taxonomicName>
, a related genus. Gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
